skitch
Homonym Number:
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:
Definition:to sool, to encourage; to set (a dog) on to an animal; sick, sool. espec. in imperative: skitch ('em); also with preps onto, towards.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim writes presumably from an English dialect. Not in DNZE or NSOD; Collins tags word as <i>NZ</i>. DEH notes: I know this from taranaki in the 40s esp. in phrase "skitch 'im"; ca1930 `skitch'm
Citations
