Source: Good Keen Man, A
Author: CRUMP
Vol / Page: 23
Edition:
Quote: I skitched [the dog] towards where the sow had buried her snout in the ground under a log. <i>Ibid.</i> 24 Even the presence of another dog would have been better encouragement than a man lumbering about trying to bark like a dog, and noisily skitching and sooling. [also p. 127]
